<p>So i need to create a transform that can return the name of the element and its value in KVP format with a tab delimeter. The trick is, I need the node itself and all its child nodes returned in teh list. Ordering is not important</p>  <p>Xml Sample:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Holding id="Holding_1"&gt;   &lt;HoldingTypeCode tc="2"&gt;PolicyType&lt;/HoldingTypeCode&gt;   &lt;HoldingStatus tc="3"&gt;ProposedStatus&lt;/HoldingStatus&gt;   &lt;Policy id="Policy_1"&gt;     &lt;PolNumber&gt;0123456789&lt;/PolNumber&gt;     &lt;LineOfBusiness tc="1"&gt;LifeBusiness&lt;/LineOfBusiness&gt;   &lt;/Policy&gt; &lt;/Holding&gt; </code></pre>  <p>In my XSLT I have this call template:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;xsl:call-template name="List_Siblings_And_Children_Recursive"&gt;   &lt;xsl:with-param name="Parent" select="//Holding"&gt;&lt;/xsl:with-param&gt; &lt;/xsl:call-template&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And this is the template itself:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;xsl:template name="List_Siblings_And_Children_Recursive"&gt; &lt;xsl:param name="Parent"&gt;&lt;/xsl:param&gt;  &lt;!-- TAB &amp; CRLF CHAR--&gt; &lt;xsl:variable name="tab"&gt;   &lt;xsl:text&gt;&amp;#x9;&lt;/xsl:text&gt; &lt;/xsl:variable&gt; &lt;xsl:variable name="CRLF"&gt;   &lt;xsl:text&gt;&amp;#10;&amp;#13;&lt;/xsl:text&gt; &lt;/xsl:variable&gt;  &lt;!-- LIST EACH ELEMENT IN THE LIST OF SIBLINGS, RECURSIVELY CHECK FOR ANY CHILDREN --&gt; &lt;xsl:for-each select="$Parent/*"&gt;   &lt;xsl:value-of select="local-name()"/&gt;   &lt;xsl:value-of select="$tab"/&gt;   &lt;xsl:value-of select="."/&gt;   &lt;xsl:value-of select="$CRLF"/&gt;   &lt;xsl:call-template name="List_Siblings_And_Children_Recursive"&gt;     &lt;xsl:with-param name="Parent" select="./*"&gt;&lt;/xsl:with-param&gt;   &lt;/xsl:call-template&gt; &lt;/xsl:for-each&gt; </code></pre>  <p></p>  <p>What is wrong with my template? The output I'm looking for should come out like:</p>  <pre><code>HoldingTypeCode    PolicyType HoldingStatus      ProposedStatus Policy PolNumber     0123456789 LineOfBusiness     LifeBusiness </code></pre>